            <h1 class="contentH1">Career Services at Medix</h1><hr class="hrp" />
            <p class="contentp">
                Employment counselling and job search training is provided for all students during their program by

                scheduled classroom lectures and ongoing individualized counselling. The School remains a permanent

                source of employment search assistance for all graduates. The placement department prepares each

                student to:
            </p>
            <ul class="contentp">
                <li>Create cover letter, resume and other effective portfolio material.</li>

                <li>Conduct an employment interview including proper follow-up activities.</li>

                <li>Analyze employment opportunities and market trends.</li>

                <li>Utilize resources for locating prospective employers.</li>

                <li>Analyze employment benefits and career advancement opportunities.</li>
            </ul>
            <br />

            <p class="contentp">
                Medix maintains a list of current and past graduates indicating their initial place of employment, along

                with completion and placement percentages. A list of past and current employers is available to all

                prospective students.
